<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 9200 9300 9400 MODELS BUILT AFTER JANUARY 1, 1995 - CATERPILLAR
        3176B/3406E ELECTRONIC ENGINE CONTROLS - 1994 - TROUBLESHOOTING - CLUTCH SWITCH (55)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="3">
        <title>CLUTCH SWITCH (55)</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the vehicle is equipped with an Allison transmission, this switch is replaced with a jumper
                        connection. Refer to paragraph
                        <hotlnk document="s08148_10.xml" xrefid="x0814836">Clutch Switch</hotlnk>
                        for description of circuit operation.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Clutch Switch And Circuits</title>
            <para>Before beginning this test procedure, inspect all connectors for loose or damaged pins, wires etc.
                (Refer to paragraph
                <hotlnk document="s08148_21.xml" xrefid="x0814828">Visual Inspection</hotlnk>
                Inspecting Connectors.)
            </para>
            <para>(Refer to
                <emph type="bold">
                    <hotlnk document="s08148_36.xml" xrefid="x0814804">CIRCUIT DIAGRAMS</hotlnk>, Figure
                    <hotlnk document="s08148_7.xml" xrefid="f0814804">6.05</hotlnk>
                    or
                    <hotlnk document="s08148_7.xml" xrefid="f0814805">6.08</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                , for this test.)
            </para>
            <figure id="f0814843" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0814843" filename="../figg08/G0814843.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption></caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0814844" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0814844" filename="../figg08/G0814844.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption></caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Adjusting Clutch Switch</title>
            <para>The Clutch switch should be mounted so that the switch actuator makes contact with the clutch pedal
                arm, when the arm is depressed 0.5 inches at the point of actuator contact. The bracket can be bent
                forward or backward for adjustment. An audible click (switch closing) should be heard when the pedal is
                released. See Illustration in
                <emph type="bold">8.0 Component Locations Figure
                    <hotlnk document="s08148_23.xml" xrefid="f0814814">8.03.</hotlnk>
                </emph>
            </para>
            <figure id="f0814845" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0814845" filename="../figg08/G0814845.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 8.03 - Clutch Switch</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
